MBOMBELA – A civilian was shot and killed and another injured this morning after CIT robbers set their visors on the KaMhlushwa Sasol Garage.  Police spokesman Brig Leonard Hlathi confirmed that a two men who were filling up their cars were shot at. One was killed and another hospitalised.”They were driving a white Ford Bantam and are still on the loose,” Hlathi said.  He urged the public to contact WO Mduduzi Shongwe on 082-359-3112 with any information that would assist the police in their investigation.